The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, July 16: India?s foreign exchange (forex) reserves fell for the third week in a row. For the week ended July 8, the reserves declined by $544 million to $136.899 billion, according to the Reserve Bank of India?s weekly statistics. The foreign currency assets declined by $529 million to $130.897 million for the reporting week. The fall is mainly due to revaluation of global currencies, analysts said.

 New Delhi, July 16: Kirloskar Brothers Ltd today said it would issue bonus shares to its shareholders in the ratio of two shares for each share held. The board has approved the issue of bonus shares, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange today. The board has also decided to increase the authorised share capital of the company from Rs 20 crore to Rs 50 crore. 

 New Delhi, July 16: Industrial Development Bank of India (IDBI) has appointed Vinod Rai, additional secretary in the ministry of finance, as the government nominee director on its board.




